reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The All Around Most Amazing Little Bag!
reviews.reviewText: I looked everywhere for a secure case that would keep my medications secured and away from our puppy, now 9 months. We should have named him Houdini the way he gets into everything he shouldn’t have and then tears around the house with it. But not this bag…this bag #1 allows me to be organized-I have Lupus and I’m on 24 medications, so being on top of what I’m taking is key. #2 the detailed compartments allow me to get in and out of an area quickly so that when my little dude is on my lap, I can get away with taking a necessary RX. #3 when it’s closed and zipped and even open and zipped, it is impossible for our dog to get into. And it’s as small as a makeup case or a tool bag!

reviews.reviewText: This bag is like a little attaché case and designed so well. It allowed me to pack a very complete kit with good quantities of items and yet it fits under the seat of my truck. It’s well made and durable. Very good price too

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, handy clear sections for all your first aid needs
reviews.reviewText: This is a really nice bag for a first aid kit, and what I like best about it is the fact that it's the only one I could find that *didn't* come with a bunch of loops and predetermined storage sections. The openness of the design meant I could fill it with whatever I needed without having to figure out how to jerryrig it all together so it would fit. My only beef with this item is that once it's completely full of stuff, it's hard to zipper shut, and I'm really straining those zippers with all I packed in. If the vinyl interior sections are packed to their full capacity, you'll have a hard time closing it. That was kind of frustrating. Other than that, it seems to be a decent bag and I love that it's a double-zipper on the outside so you can quickly access your things. Great first aid bag!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my dogs' first aid kit
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a good bag to hold and organize first aid supplies for our pups. This bag is perfect! It's just the right size to hold everything (except one wide bottle of activated charcoal powder). I have an assortment of single use gels, ointments, that sort of thing in one flap, a muzzle in the other flap, a soft cone in the largest pocket, and the other two large pockets hold bandages, Benadryl, styptic powder, and antiseptic spray. It's easy to stick in the car when we go on hikes or trips.
